ic":"Money","qtype":"money and currency","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/19 Q05","year":2019,"session":"March","tex":"A tourist changes \\$500 to euros (€) when the exchange rate is €1 = \\$1.0697.\n\nCalculate how many euros he receives.\n\n€","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019March-Paper22-Q06","paper":"2019March-Paper22","qnum":6,"marks":2,"topics":["Number","Probability"],"s":"1.1","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Types of number","qtype":"types of number","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/19 Q06","year":2019,"session":"March","tex":"The probability that a sweet made in a factory is the wrong shape is 0.0028.\nOne day, the factory makes 25 000 sweets.\n\nCalculate the number of sweets that are expected to be the wrong shape.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019March-Paper22-Q07","paper":"2019March-Paper22","qnum":7,"marks":2,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.3","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Scale drawings and bearings","qtype":"scale drawings and bearings","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/19 Q07","year":2019,"session":"March","tex":"The bearing of Alexandria from Paris is $128^\\circ$.\n\nCalculate the bearing of Paris from Alexandria.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019March-Paper22-Q08","paper":"2019March-Paper22","qnum":8,"marks":2,"topics":["Transformations and vectors"],"s":"7.3","d":2,"cat":"vectors","topic":"Magnitude of a vector","qtype":"magnitude and unit vectors","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/19 Q08","year":2019,"session":"March","tex":"O is the origin, $\\overrightarrow{OA} = 2\\mathbf{x} + 3\\mathbf{y}$ and $\\overrightarrow{BA} = \\mathbf{x} - 4\\mathbf{y}$.\n\nFind the position vector of B, in terms of $\\mathbf{x}$ and $\\mathbf{y}$, in its simplest form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2019March-Paper22-Q09","paper":"2019March-Paper22","qnum":9,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra a