 Q13","year":2019,"session":"March","tex":"Factorise.\n\n(a) $7k^2 - 15k$\n\n(b) $12(m + p) + 8(m + p)^2$","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2019March-Paper22-Q14","paper":"2019March-Paper22","qnum":14,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.13","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Percentages","qtype":"percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/19 Q14","year":2019,"session":"March","tex":"Eric invests an amount in a bank that pays compound interest at a rate of 2.16\\% per year.\nAt the end of 5 years, the value of his investment is \\$6999.31.\n\nCalculate the amount Eric invests.\n\n\\$","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019March-Paper22-Q15","paper":"2019March-Paper22","qnum":15,"marks":3,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.7","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Circle theorems","qtype":"circle theorems","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/19 Q15","year":2019,"session":"March","tex":"%\\begin{InsertScreenShot}\n%    \n%\\end{InsertScreenShot}\n\nA, B and C are points on the circle, centre O.\nAB and OC intersect at P.\n\nFind the value of w.\n\nw =","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2019March-Paper22-Q16","paper":"2019March-Paper22","qnum":16,"marks":3,"topics":["Number","Coordinate geometry","Geometry","Trigonometry"],"s":"1.9","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Estimation","qtype":"estimation and rounding","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/19 Q16","year":2019,"session":"March","tex":"%\\begin{InsertScreenShot}\n%    \n%\\end{InsertScreenShot}\n\nBy drawing a suitable tangent, estimate the gradient of the curve at the point P.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019March-Paper22-Q17","paper":"2019March-Paper22","qnum":17,"marks":3,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","