":4,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/19 Q21","year":2019,"session":"March","tex":"Without using a calculator, work out $\\dfrac{15}{8} \\times \\dfrac{12}{5}$.\nYou must show all your working and give your answer as a mixed number in its simplest form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019March-Paper22-Q22","paper":"2019March-Paper22","qnum":22,"marks":4,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.12","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Rates","qtype":"rates","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/19 Q22","year":2019,"session":"March","tex":"%\\begin{InsertScreenShot}\n%    \n%\\end{InsertScreenShot}\n\nThe speed--time graph shows the first 50 seconds of a journey.\n\nCalculate\n\n(a) the acceleration during the first 15 seconds,\n\n(b) the distance travelled in the 50 seconds.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":3}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2019March-Paper22-Q23","paper":"2019March-Paper22","qnum":23,"marks":6,"topics":["Coordinate geometry","Geometry"],"s":"3.7","d":2,"cat":"coord","topic":"Perpendicular lines","qtype":"perpendicular lines","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/19 Q23","year":2019,"session":"March","tex":"A is the point (2, 3) and B is the point (7, -5).\n\n(a) Find the co-ordinates of the midpoint of AB.\n\n(, )\n\n(b) Find the equation of the line through A that is perpendicular to AB.\nGive your answer in the form y = mx + c.\n\ny =","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":4}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2019March-Paper22-Q24","paper":"2019March-Paper22","qnum":24,"marks":7,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.13","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Percentages","qtype":"percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/M/19 Q24","year":2019,"session":"March","tex":"%\\begin{InsertScreenShot}\n%    \n%\\end{InsertS